President Trump and Prime Minister Abe of Japan held a meeting at Mar-a-Lago in Florida to discuss various topics including North Korea, military cooperation, and trade. Trump expressed his desire to reduce the trade deficit with Japan and mentioned the large orders of airplanes that Japan has placed with the United States. Trump also introduced Larry Kudlow and John Bolton as part of his team. Prime Minister Abe thanked Trump for the warm welcome and the good relationship between the two countries. Trump emphasized the need for reciprocal trade agreements and highlighted the imbalance in trade with countries like China. He expressed confidence in Mike Pompeo's confirmation as Secretary of State and praised his recent meeting with Kim Jong-un in North Korea.